SIMPLE: rustic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rustic
<hw>Rus"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rusticus</ets>, fr. <ets>rus</ets>, <ets>ruris</ets>, the country:
cf. F. <ets>rustique</ets>. See <er>Rural</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to the country; rural; <as>as, the <ex>rustic</ex>
gods of antiquity</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Rustic</xex> lays.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And many a holy text around she strews,⟦br⟧
That teach the <qex>rustic</qex> moralist to die.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She had a <qex>rustic</qex>, woodland air.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rude; awkward; rough; unpolished; <as>as,
<ex>rustic</ex> manners</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>rustic</xex>
muse.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Coarse; plain; simple; <as>as, a <ex>rustic</ex>
entertainment; <ex>rustic</ex> dress</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Simple; artless; unadorned; unaffected.</def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Rustic moth</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any moth
belonging to <gen>Agrotis</gen> and allied genera. Their larvae are
called <xex>cutworms</xex>. See <er>Cutworm</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Rustic
work</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <cd>Cut stone facing
which has the joints worked with grooves or channels, the face of each
block projecting beyond the joint, so that the joints are very
conspicuous</cd>. <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Arch. & Woodwork)</fld> <cd>Summer
houses, or furniture for summer houses, etc., made of rough limbs of
trees fancifully arranged.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Rural; rude; unpolished; inelegant; untaught;
awkward; rough; coarse; plain; unadorned; simple; artless; honest. See
<er>Rural</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rustic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rustic
<hw>Rus"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An inhabitant of the
country, especially one who is rude, coarse, or dull; a clown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hence to your fields, you <qex>rustics</qex>! hence, away.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rural person having a natural simplicity of
character or manners; an artless, unaffected person.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rustical</ent>⟦br⟧
